article.description: Senior centers Chay Shegog and Laura Broomfield each had double-doubles for North Carolina (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) in a 109-44 rout of Gardner-Webb on Saturday.
article.headline: Chay Shegog ties career high with 19 points in Tar Heels' win
article.linkText: Shegog, Broomfield lead North Carolina in rout
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. --  Senior centers Chay Shegog and Laura Broomfield each had double-doubles for North Carolina (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) in a 109-44 rout of Gardner-Webb on Saturday.

Shegog tied her career high with 19 points and had 10 rebounds, and Broomfield added 15 points and 14 rebounds .

Freshman wing Megan Buckland had 17 points in her first start for North Carolina, while Danielle Butts had 12.

Catrina Green and KiKi Smith had 10 points each for Gardner-Webb.

North Carolina, which leads the series 3-0, led 62-26 at halftime behind 11 points from Shegog.

UNC shot 46 percent and outrebounded the Runnin' Bulldogs' 62-40.
